🏔️ **Vermont White-tailed Deer Predictions** - Enhanced grid analysis for rut season.

📊 **How to Read the Score Heatmaps:**
• **Red areas (8-10)**: Excellent deer activity - prime hunting locations
• **Yellow areas (6-7)**: Good deer activity - solid hunting spots
• **Blue areas (0-5)**: Lower deer activity - less productive areas

🎯 **Activity Markers Guide:**
• **Travel Markers (Blue)**: Point markers showing prime travel corridors - ideal for morning/evening hunts
• **Bedding Markers (Red)**: Point markers for top bedding areas in thick cover, especially thick cover near travel routes
• **Feeding Markers (Green)**: Point markers for feeding areas near standing corn, remaining soybeans, high-energy browse and mast crops
• **🎯 Stand Locations (⭐)**: Star markers positioned strategically to intercept deer moving between activity areas
• **🏹 Mature Buck Assessment**: Location below threshold for mature buck targeting (terrain suitability: 38.5%)

• **Hunting Advantage**: Morning Ridge
• 🌄 Prime thermal hunting window
• ❄️ Cool air flows downhill - scent predictable
• 🎯 Position on ridges/upper slopes
• **🎯 Vermont Strategy**: Position on ridges/upper slopes - scent carries away from deer below
• **⏰ Timing**: Best 30-60 minutes after first light when thermals are strongest

🌬️ **Tomorrow's Wind Forecast**:
• **Dominant Wind**: South at 13.3 mph
• **Best Morning Window**: 5:00 - South wind at 10.4 mph

• **Wind Advice**: Moderate winds - plan stand locations carefully

📅 **Rut Season Strategy:**
• Focus on travel corridors (red areas) - bucks are moving extensively
• Hunt saddles, ridge connections, and funnels
• Morning and evening movement peaks
